Question : Find out if two strings are anagram of each other. 

Solution : 
Converting into array and sorting and comparing. 
Sol: import java.util.*;
public class MyClass {
  public static void main(String args[]) {
    String a = "silent";
    String b = "listen";
    
    char[] a_arr = a.toCharArray();
    char[] b_arr = b.toCharArray();

    Arrays.sort(a_arr);
    Arrays.sort(b_arr);

    if (Arrays.equals(a_arr, b_arr)) {
        System.out.println("true");
    } else {
        System.out.println("false");
    }
  }
}

Things I learnt --> 
1. Difference between ==, .equals(), Array.equals()
== --> Compares memory address (reference), not content. 
.equals -->  Same as == (reference check), unless overridden.
Arrays.equals() --> Static method â†’ Arrays content is compared, element-by-element. Works for primitive arrays aur object arrays.

2. Arrays.sort() does not return anything (its return type is void).
It sorts the given array in place, meaning it modifies the original array directly instead of creating and returning a new sorted array.
